                    <h3>Password Protection</h3>
                    <p>Add an extra layer of security by setting a password for your shared files. Recipients will need to enter the password before they can download the files.</p>
                    
                    <div class="warning-box">
                        <strong>Important:</strong> Store passwords securely and share them through a different communication channel than the download link.
                    </div>
                    
                    <h2>Using the API</h2>
                    <p>For developers who want to integrate DropLaa into their applications, we provide a comprehensive REST API.</p>
                    
                    <h3>Authentication</h3>
                    <p>API requests require authentication using an API key. You can generate API keys from your account dashboard.</p>
                    
                    <div class="code-block">
curl -X POST "https://api.droplaa.com/v1/upload" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
  -F "file=@/path/to/your/file.pdf"
                    </div>
                    
                    <h3>Upload Endpoint</h3>
                    <p>The <span class="inline-code">POST /v1/upload</span> endpoint allows you to upload files programmatically.</p>
                    
                    <h2>Mobile Applications</h2>
                    <p>DropLaa is available on both iOS and Android platforms. The mobile apps provide the same security and features as the web platform, optimized for mobile use.</p>
                    
                    <h3>Key Mobile Features</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Upload files directly from your camera roll</li>
                        <li>Share files from other apps using the share sheet</li>
                        <li>Receive push notifications when files are downloaded</li>
                        <li>Offline viewing of download history</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h2>Troubleshooting Common Issues</h2>
                    
                    <h3>Upload Failures</h3>
                    <p>If your upload fails, try these solutions:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Check your internet connection</li>
                        <li>Ensure the file size is within your plan limits</li>
                        <li>Try uploading one file at a time</li>
                        <li>Clear your browser cache and cookies</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h3>Slow Upload Speeds</h3>
                    <p>To improve upload speeds:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Use a wired internet connection instead of Wi-Fi</li>
                        <li>Close other applications using bandwidth</li>
                        <li>Upload during off-peak hours</li>
                        <li>Consider compressing large files before upload</li>
                    </ul>
                    
